ch used a clocked `always` block for checking, so I will maintain that structure for sampling, even though the DUT is combinatorial, as this is what the original TB used to drive its statistics.\n*   The original testbench had a complex comparison: `assign tb_match = ( { out_ref } === ( { out_ref } ^ { out_dut } ^ { out_ref } ) );`. This simplifies to `tb_match = (out_ref === out_dut)`. I will use the simple equality check for clarity while preserving the intent.",
